## Accumulated Context

### Decisions

Decisions are logged in PROJECT.md Key Decisions table.
Recent decisions affecting current work:

- v1.3: Cowork audit → Claude Code pipeline for external review + automated fixes
- All milestones: Backwards compatible changes only (no breaking changes)
- Supabase Edge Functions deployment only (no Vercel for backend)
- Phase 18: 8 tables in Drizzle schema don't exist in production DB (schema/DB mismatch discovered)
- Phase 19-01: Use Next.js 'server-only' package for build-time enforcement rather than runtime checks
- Phase 19-01: Apply server-only guard to all modules accessing SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
- Phase 19-02: Use throw Error() for server actions (not NextResponse which is for API routes)
- Phase 19-02: All server actions must check session before any operation
- Phase 19-02: Verify chat ownership through RLS-compatible userId filtering pattern
- Phase 20-01: CLI scripts use minimal console.log (task name + completion status only)
- Phase 20-01: Production Next.js code (app/) must have ZERO console.log statements
- Phase 20-01: JSDoc @example blocks may contain console.log in documentation
- Phase 20-03: Use z.literal(true) for exact boolean confirmation (not truthy values)
- Phase 20-03: Use parse() in server actions (throws ZodError), safeParse() in API routes (returns Result)
- Phase 20-03: Use z.custom() for complex AI SDK types already typed by TypeScript

### Pending Todos

- Sync Drizzle schema with production DB (8 tables defined but not migrated)
- Repair supabase migration history (local/remote mismatch)

### Blockers/Concerns

- Schema/DB mismatch: PropertyListing, LandListing, ZyprusAgent, AgentChatSession, ListingUploadAttempt, DocumentSend, AdminAuditLog, AgentExecutionLog exist in schema.ts but not in production
- Migration history: `supabase db push` won't work until local/remote migration history is reconciled

